<subSubSection pageId="13" pageNumber="84" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1437,151,1149]" pageId="13" pageNumber="84">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,1087,1113]" pageId="13" pageNumber="84">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific epithet is derived from the Latin 
<emphasis box="[845,909,1087,1113]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="84">ferro-</emphasis>
and 
<emphasis box="[962,1020,1087,1113]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="84">rufus</emphasis>
, referring to the forewing having two ferrugineous red patches.
</paragraph>
